data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** The syntax is straightforward:

```csharp
Span<nint>  s = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> u = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

The only caveat encountered: `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since `nint` doesn't have a compile-time–known size), but `stackalloc` itself works fine in safe code when assigned to a `Span<T>`.
